<P>
   KOSOVO (Prugovac, Yugoslavia) _ The activity in Prugovac is a
typical operation for the Yugoslav army and police forces: A sniper
shoots and wounds an army officer driving his jeep down the main
road at mid-morning, and the security forces react swiftly and with
full force. A few miles west, a group of ethnic Albanian villagers
stand waiting for a bus outside the village of Stanovac. As they
talk beside the road, gunfire crackles behind them. No one even
flinches. By Carlotta Gall.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Locator map has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
