<P>
   INDIANS-RESORTS (Bernalillo, N.M.) _ After using casino gambling
over the past several years to help reverse their fortunes, Native
American tribes are now beginning to build an entire leisure
industry on their reservations. But as the easy-money aura of
vacation resorts, gambling, golf and shopping spreads across the
land that these people have for centuries defended, worshipped and
fervently protected from outside intrusion, concern is growing
among tribal members that their religion, culture and sovereignty
are being pushed aside. By Brett Pulley.
</P>
