<HEADER>
A1937 &Cx1f; tth-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-KARL-FINED-SPI &LR;      03-16 0420
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-KARL-FINED-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMMENTS PROVE COSTLY FOR GEORGE KARL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By RONALD TILLERY  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE _ Former Sonics coach George Karl had a mouthful of
comments about his old bosses last week.
</P>
<P>
   Now Karl, who coaches the Milwaukee Bucks, has his hands full.
</P>
<P>
   On the day that the NBA fined the Bucks $25,000 for bitter
remarks Karl made about Sonics president Wally Walker, the
Post-Intelligencer learned that Karl is going through a divorce.
Cathy Karl, his wife of 21{ years, petitioned for a divorce Feb. 5
in King County Superior Court. In court records, the reason for
dissolution is that the marriage had been ``irretrievably broken.''
</P>
<P>
   Karl, whose contract was not renewed by the Sonics after last
season, has lived in a Milwaukee hotel since he signed a four-year,
$20 million deal with the Bucks last August. Cathy Karl has
remained in Seattle and maintains the couple's Bellevue home.
</P>
<P>
   Though the NBA repeatedly had warned Karl about criticizing the
Sonics, Karl called Walker ``incompetent'' in a story that appeared
in the P-I last Wednesday. Karl's team then beat the Sonics that
night.
</P>
<P>
   Karl and Walker often feuded during their time together in
Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   John Calipari, who was fired by the New Jersey Nets on Monday,
is the only other coach to receive such a hefty fine for comments
directed toward anyone other than league officials. Calipari was
fined $25,000 for offensive comments made toward a reporter.
</P>
<P>
   ``If they felt I was hurting the league, I'm sorry that they
felt that way,'' Karl told reporters before Monday night's game
between the Bucks and the New York Knicks in Milwaukee. ``The thing
that makes me sad is that I think I said 90 percent awful positive
things about my time in Seattle and about the team there because I
have a lot of love for the team,'' Karl said.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's one human being there that I have problems with,'' he
said. ``I guess they don't want me talking about that.''
</P>
<P>
   Karl has not talked publicly about his impending divorce. The
court documents had just one signature: Cathy Karl's.
</P>
<P>
   A trial date is set for Dec. 27 if a settlement isn't reached by
then. Cathy Karl is seeking alimony, child support and equitable
division of property. She refused comment Monday and her attorney,
Evan Schwab, did not return phone messages.
</P>
<P>
   Cathy and George Karl were married Aug. 5, 1977 in Nampa, Idaho.
They have two children _ Kelci, 19, and Coby, 15.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-16-99 0213EST &QL; 
