</P>
<P>
   (PAGE INCLUDES 1 COLOR PHOTO, 1 COLOR MUG SHOT)
</P>
<P>
   The folks at Pontiac could have left well enough alone with the
Grand Am. Since its 1992 redesign, the nameplate has ranked as one
of the 10 most popular cars in the United States. And with annual
sales in excess of 200,000, the Pontiac has led the compact class
in retail registrations for the past five years. Yet the automaker
unveiled a new design for 1999. (Includes 3-column color photo of
Grand Am)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: AT A GLANCE: Fact box on the Pontiac Grand Am.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: THE MECHANIC: Getting your car repaired? Pick any two:
good, fast or cheap. (Includes 1-column color mug shot of
columnist)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PERSONAL TECHNOLOGY: SHOULD YOU BUY A PC WITH PENTIUM III? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (PAGE INCLUDES 2 COLOR PHOTOS)
</P>
<P>
   PCs with the new Pentium III chip from Intel are on shelves now.
These new machines are the fastest yet, reasonably priced and _
based on early reports _ relatively bug-free. Just don't buy one.
(Includes 3-column color photo of chip)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: FACT BOX: Facts about the new Pentium III chip.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECH BRIEFS: Sports teams have had their own Web sites
since the Internet became popular. Now individual players are
taking the cue. For example, there's The Official Tim Duncan
Website of the San Antonio Spurs second-year power forward.
(Includes 2-column color photo of web site)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECHNOBUDDY: As soon as they're available in your
neighborhood _ and if you have the money to spare _ get a cable
modem and use it to connect to the Internet. That's what I did a
week ago. It made a big difference, but maybe not in the ways you'd
expect.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: ON-LINE LIFE: This year's hot technology trend is
compelling content from media players such as newspapers,
magazines, television networks and cable companies.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: INTERNET NOTES: One of the most popular instruments for
amateur musicians is the guitar. As it turns out, the Web is a
terrific resource for would-be guitar players.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TRAVEL: EUROPE'S MOST ROMANTIC CITIES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (PAGE INCLUDES 4 COLOR PHOTOS)
</P>
<P>
   Columnist offers picks for the most romantic cities in Europe
plus advice for those planning a honeymoon: First, stay in one
place in Europe. Don't go driving all over the continent in an
effort to see everything. You'll just get tired and cranky. Stay in
one city, and it will become ``your'' city, the one that will be
foremost in your photo album. (Includes main art of couple riding a
gondola in Venice plus secondary art of gondolier; color photo of
