<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With BLIND. For release Sunday, March 21.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARE YOU VISION-IMPAIRED?
</P>
<P>
   Here are two rules of thumb for persons wearing glasses or
contact lenses.
</P>
<P>
   _ If you have trouble reading newsprint or recognizing a friend
across the room, or are blind in one eye, you have a vision
impairment.
</P>
<P>
   _ If you can't read newsprint or recognize a friend at arm's
length, or are blind in both eyes, your impairment is ``severe.''
</P>
<P>
   AMERICANS WITH VISION HANDICAPS, PER THOUSAND
</P>
<P>
   AGE GROUP 
..................................................6-20......21-64...
...65 or older
</P>
<P>
   Persons with severe vision impairments ...........
1...........4.............30
</P>
<P>
   Persons with moderate vision impairments .....
10..........23...........103
</P>
<P>
   Source: Census Bureau estimates.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOLOGY ADVICE FOR THE VISUALLY IMPAIRED
</P>
<P>
   American Foundation for the Blind, New York.
</P>
<P>
   Offers lists of technology aids, suppliers and price ranges, as
well as technical reviews of competing products. Provides access to
visually impaired volunteers who discuss technology issues by phone
or E-mail.
</P>
<P>
   Internet: http://www.afb.org
</P>
<P>
   Phone: 800-AFB-LINE (232-5463)
</P>
<P>
   Lighthouse International, New York.
</P>
<P>
   Services include catalogs of low-vision gadgets, as well as
referrals to clinics where you can try out software or devices that
might work for you.
</P>
<P>
   Internet: http://www.lighthouse.org
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: info(at)lighthouse.org
</P>
<P>
   Phone: 800-829-0500
</P>
<P>
   National Federation for the Blind, Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
   The nation's largest membership organization of the blind offers
phone numbers and addresses for affiliates, useful libraries,
rehabilitation agencies and other resources near your home.
</P>
<P>
   Internet: http://www.nfb.org/services.htm
</P>
<P>
   Phone: 410-659-9314
</P>
<P>
   American Council of the Blind, Washington.
</P>
<P>
   The nation's second largest membership organization of the blind
offers lists of low-tech and high-tech vendors and products, and
updates on new legislative, regulatory and technical developments.
</P>
<P>
   Internet: http://www.acb.org
</P>
<P>
   Phone: 800-424-8666
</P>
<P>
   Technical Assistance Center, West Virginia University.
</P>
<P>
   This federally funded project puts you in touch with state
centers designed to help businesses, workers and rehabilitation
agencies learn how technology can make disabled workers more
productive without undue expense.
</P>
<P>
   Internet: http://www.adata.org/dbtac.htm
</P>
<P>
   Phone: 800-949-4232
</P>
<P>
   MOST POPULAR WEB SITES PRESENT PROBLEMS TO VISUALLY IMPAIRED
</P>
<P>
   All but five of the 25 Web sites that had the most visitors in
January had some elements that could not be understood by the
special technology that allows visually impaired users to surf the
Internet. In most cases, the programmers failed to include text
alternatives to graphic elements, such as submit buttons or
click-on images.
</P>
<P>
   Web site ................. Number of problems
</P>
<P>
   real.com ........................ 75
</P>
<P>
   aol.com ......................... 55
</P>
<P>
   go.com .......................... 48
</P>
<P>
   altavista.com.................. 32
</P>
<P>
   xoom.com ..................... 22
</P>
<P>
   amazon.com .................. 18
</P>
<P>
   zdnet.com ..................... 18
</P>
<P>
   bluemountainarts.com ......15
</P>
<P>
   weather.com .................. 14
</P>
<P>
   hotbot.com .................... 13
</P>
<P>
   tripod.com .....................12
</P>
<P>
   infospace.com ................ 10
</P>
<P>
   netscape.com .................. 8
</P>
<P>
   lycos.com ....................... 8
</P>
<P>
   angelfire.com .................. 7
</P>
<P>
   snap.com ....................... 7
</P>
<P>
   yahoo.com ..................... 5
</P>
<P>
   excite.com ..................... 2
</P>
<P>
   geocities.com ................. 1
</P>
<P>
   ebay.com ...................... 1
</P>
<P>
   msn.com ....................... 0
</P>
<P>
   microsoft.com ................ 0
</P>
<P>
   hotmail.com ................... 0
</P>
<P>
   msnbc.com .................... 0
</P>
<P>
   icq.com ......................... 0
</P>
<P>
   Method: List of the 25 Web sites with the most visitors in
January was compiled by Media Metrix Inc. On March 10, Cox
Newspapers tested the home page of each site, using a Web-based
service (http://www.cast.org/bobby) of the Center for Applied
Special Technology. The service analyzes Web pages for their
accessibility to people with disabilities. The analyses were based
on the latest working draft of the voluntary guidelines for HTML
4.0. The guidelines are being developed by the W3C's WAI Page
Authoring Working Group.
</P>
