   BOX-BERKOW-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports of The Times column: As
the history of the sport makes clear, the appeal of boxing is
rooted in its corrupt nature. The Holyfield-Lewis draw is just
another chapter. By Ira Berkow.
</P>
