   NKOREA-NUKE (Washington) _ The United States and North Korea
ended months of negotiations Tuesday with an agreement that gives
American nuclear inspectors access to a huge underground site that
Washington suspects is the centerpiece of a renewed North Korean
effort to build atomic weapons. The deal includes some modest
commitments by the United States to continue food aid to North
Korea. By David E. Sanger.
</P>
