Serbian province of Kosovo approached impasse Tuesday. Serbian
negotiators refused to accept a NATO peacekeeping force and
insisted on extensive changes to the proposed peace settlement, but
international mediators rejected any substantive changes to the
agreement. By Craig R. Whitney.
