a bill to protect Medicaid patients from being ``dumped'' out of
nursing homes in favor of patients who pay only through private
funds. (400 words.) By C.J. Karamargin
</P>
<P>
   LOUISIANA-BREAUX-MEDICARE. As a bipartisan Medicare commission
gets set to vote tonight on Sen. John Breaux's plan to overhaul the
nation's elderly and disabled program, members appear virtually
certain to break entirely along partisan lines when casting their
votes, thus dashing hopes that the commission could craft a
compromise on reform. (450 words.) By Mark Stricherz
