<P>
   DOW HITS 10,000
</P>
<P>
   DOW-MAGICMARK _ The Dow Jones industrial average opened on the
downside today but quickly mounted a furious rally and passed the
magic 10,000 mark at 9:51 a.m. before retreating. Traders and
analysts compared the milestone to the breaking of the sound
barrier and reaching the moon. ``I never thought I'd see this,''
marvelled Larry Wachtel, a veteran analyst for Prudential
Securities. ``I am 66, have been on the Street 38 years, and this
is really something.'' (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in the (f) Financial and (a) General News
categories.
</P>
<P>
   w/DOW-FUTURE _ ATLANTA _ Okay, what next? Now that the Dow Jones
industrial average has traded above 10,000 for the first time,
investors would like to know if it will close above that benchmark
level any time soon, drop back or go even higher.
</P>
<P>
   (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOW-HISTORY _ ATLANTA _ The Dow rises, the Dow falls, the Dow
remains unchanged, but most of all, the Dow makes news _ and in the
latest case, history. The Dow, of course, is the Dow Jones
industrial average. Why it should get so much attention is a matter
of considerable debate, between those who see the Dow at 10,000 as
historic and those who see 10,000 as ``just a number.'' (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOW-CHANGE _ ATLANTA _ Investing used to be dominated by men. No
longer. One telling sign: Women now make up 68 percent of the
membership of the National Association of Investors Corp., which
represents 733,000 individual and investment club members. There's
also evidence that women make better investors than men, according
to data compiled by the NAIC, which is based in Madison Heights,
Mich. (Joyner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOW _PSYCHO _ ATLANTA _ Why are we interested in benchmark
events like the Dow 1,000 or 5,000 or 10,000 _ or the year 2000?
Why not 9,999? Psychologists say it has something to do with
reflecting on our lives at key points and measuring ourselves
against these benchmarks. (Hendrick, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOW-INTERNET_ ATLANTA _ A look at how the increase in making
trades over the Internet has helped propel the Dow to new heights.
(Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOW-FOUR _ ATANTA _ A look at the impact of the growth of
company 401k plans on the stock market's rise. (Ezell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
