<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Val-Pak is new online source for coupons
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Yahoo! has signed up Val-Pak as a source of local
coupons on its new site, coupons.yahoo. The site offers Internet
users the opportunity to find and print out coupons to national and
local stores.
</P>
<P>
   Val-Pak, a unit of Atlanta-based Cox Target Media, has developed
a database of coupons searchable via the Web by local ZIP codes. In
other words, a consumer in Atlanta could find a coupon to his or
her nearest Subway sandwich shop.
</P>
<P>
   ``By working with Yahoo!, we are giving their 50 million users
simplified access to the wide variety of coupons available from
Val-Pak,'' said Todd Leiser, vice president of Internet technology
at Cox Target Media.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Based in Largo, Fla., Val-Pak is a direct mailer of coupon
packages nationwide. The company maintains its own Web site at
http://www.valpak.com. Yahoo! can be found at http://www.yahoo.com.
</P>
<P>
   Cox Target Media is a unit of Cox Enterprises Inc., a private
company that also owns The Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Charles Haddad writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
