<P>
   OLY-SCANDAL (Lausanne, Switzerland) _ US Senator John McCain
tells the International Olympic Committee it is ``critical that the
IOC understand the gravity of this situation,'' referring to the
bribery scandal that has rocked the organization. By John Powers.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-PROP16 (Undated) _ The NCAA receives another legal
setback when a federal judge denies a request to delay the
enforcement of a court order wiping out minimum standardized test
scores as a requirement for freshman eligibility. By Mark
Blaudschun.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-BRUINS (Boston) _ With his team in crunch time, vying for
the eighth and final playoff position, the pressure is magnified
for goalie Byron Dafoe, especially on the road. By Marvin Pave.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-CELTICS (Boston) _ Prior to acquiring Vitaly Potapenko last
week, the Celtics' two biggest interior weaknesses were rebounding
and shot-blocking. Now that they have Potapenko, their two biggest
interior weaknesses are rebounding and shot-blocking. By Peter May.
800 words.
</P>
