r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CNS-BOXING-GOLDEN-GLO     03-16 1171
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CNS-BOXING-GOLDEN-GLOVES </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE GOLDEN GLOVES: BOXERS FIGHT FOR A DREAM 
</HEADLINE>
   For use by New York Times Syndicate/News Service clients as
desired.  
 By ADAM KRAMER  
 c. 1999 Columbia News Service   ``Watching a fight on television
has always seemed to me a poor substitute for being there. For one
thing, you can't tell the fighters what to do. When I watch a
fight, I like to study one boxer's problem, solve it, and then
communicate my solution vocally.'' -- A.J. Liebling
<TEXT>
