gambles that a European car company has ever taken, Renault SA of
France offered Tuesday to buy 35 percent of Nissan Motor Co.,
Japan's huge but deeply troubled producer of cars and trucks. If
accepted by Nissan, the deal would transform Renault from a
smallish European producer into one of the auto industry's biggest
