Chicago, just 90 minutes before, and their train was due to pull
into New Orleans in the late afternoon of the next day. But in an
instant, everything changed. At 9:30 p.m. Monday, Amtrak's City of
New Orleans smashed into a semi-trailer truck at a railroad
crossing in this rural town. By Tuesday afternoon, 14 passengers
were known dead, all of them in the sleeper car. By Pam Belluck.
