Kluger, the orchestra's president, says he realizes that the label
``20th-century music'' often conjures up ``a stereotype of music
that is ... atonal, and harshly dissonant.'' But, he is quick to
point out that this century also has its share of ``popular and
accessible'' works. (Ozier Muhammad/New York Times Photo)
