University last year, with two of the people in her Oscar-nominated
documentary, Selma Wernick and Harold Gordon. ``It's really
surreal,'' Ms. Ibi, 32, says of the nomination of her film, ``The
Personals: Improvisations on Romance in the Golden Years,'' and the
flurry of telephone calls and E-mail media interviews it has
spawned. (Linda Rosier/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) ASBURY PARK, N.J. -- March 16, 1999 -- HEAVY-METAL-2,
3-16 -- Fans enjoying the music during ``March Metal Meltdown'' in
Asbury Park. Contrary to what might be expected there were plenty
of women in attendance; the grimmer sub-genres of metal have a lot
of female fans, perhaps because the lyrics do not usually carry a
sexist aggressiveness. (Nicole Bengiveno/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) ASBURY PARK, N.J. -- March 16, 1999 -- HEAVY-METAL-1,
3-16 -- Matthew Barlow of Iced Earth at ``March Metal Meltdown'' in
Asbury Park. Metal has evolved at a creeping pace, its various
splintered genres hanging on through waxing and waning demands for
it in the marketplace. (Nicole Bengiveno/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) NEW YORK -- March 16, 1999 -- AMISH-COOKING-2, 3-16 -- In
New York, horse-drawn buggies carry tourists, not the Amish. Yet
Amish food has gained a certain cachet. The Amish Manhattan Farmers
Market on Ninth Avenue, whose owners are from Turkey, will hang its
third horse-and-buggy shingle in New York at the World Trade Center
in May. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) NEW YORK -- March 16, 1999 -- AMISH-COOKING-1, 3-16 -- In
New York, horse-drawn buggies carry tourists, not the Amish. Yet
Amish food has gained a certain cachet. The logo of the Amish
Manhattan Farmers Market on Ninth Avenue, whose owners are from
Turkey. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) LAS VEGAS -- March 16, 1999 -- WINE-TALK, 3-16 -- Barrie
Larvin, the wine buyer at the Rio Hotel in Las Vegas, values the
cellar there at more than $6 million. ``We go through a case of
first growths every weekend,'' says Larvi, referring to five of the
top Bordeaux chateaus. Move over, Paris. Move over, New York. When
it comes to wine, Las Vegas is the place to be: a city with an
unquenchable thirst. (John Gurzinski/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- March 16, 1999 -- LAYER-CAKE-2, 3-16 --
Yellow buttermilk cake with chocolate frosting at Magnolia Bakery.
At today's prices - and at the current level of competition in
pastry kitchens - it takes a confident chef to give layer cake a
try. (Kyoshi Togashi/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- March 16, 1999 -- LAYER-CAKE-1, 3-16 -- At
the Magnolia Bakery in Greenwich Village, the layer cakes are
coconut, chocolate, German chocolate or pink buttercream. The wedge
of layer cake - with its precisely contrasted flavors and textures,
its perfect proportion of crumb to buttercream - is a stellar
representative of confectionary harmony. But it's just no dazzler.
(Kyoshi Togashi/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
