   (NYT3) LAS VEGAS -- March 16, 1999 -- WINE-TALK, 3-16 -- Barrie
Larvin, the wine buyer at the Rio Hotel in Las Vegas, values the
cellar there at more than $6 million. ``We go through a case of
first growths every weekend,'' says Larvi, referring to five of the
top Bordeaux chateaus. Move over, Paris. Move over, New York. When
it comes to wine, Las Vegas is the place to be: a city with an
unquenchable thirst. (John Gurzinski/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- March 16, 1999 -- LAYER-CAKE-2, 3-16 --
Yellow buttermilk cake with chocolate frosting at Magnolia Bakery.
At today's prices - and at the current level of competition in
pastry kitchens - it takes a confident chef to give layer cake a
try. (Kyoshi Togashi/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- March 16, 1999 -- LAYER-CAKE-1, 3-16 -- At
the Magnolia Bakery in Greenwich Village, the layer cakes are
coconut, chocolate, German chocolate or pink buttercream. The wedge
of layer cake - with its precisely contrasted flavors and textures,
its perfect proportion of crumb to buttercream - is a stellar
representative of confectionary harmony. But it's just no dazzler.
(Kyoshi Togashi/New York Times Photo)
</P>
