<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, March 17. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
SLUM-LAW _ A law designed to root out slumlords, one of the
toughest in the nation, passed the Arizona Legislature on Tuesday
and is on its way to Gov. Jane Hull, who is expected to sign it.
The legislation requires property owners or agents to register with
the county assessors' offices, increases penalties for landlords
who don't clean up their property, and gives cities and counties
new powers against owners of property used for criminal activity.
By PAT KOSSAN. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
